WARRI  – A suspected ‘Yahoo Boy’ has reportedly crushed two motor mechanics to death in a fatal accident along the Ughelli Effurun expressway in Ughelli, Delta State. Five others, including a driver of a tricycle otherwise known as Keke and four occu­pants of the vehicle survived the accident with life-threat­ening injuries. The accident occurred on the busy Ekiugbo town junc­tion in Ughelli. Gunmen Shoot Dead Vigilante Commander In Delta Alleged Ineptitude: Angry Onicha-Ugbo Youths Protest Against… It was gathered that the suspected Yahoo boy in com­pany of four others were re­turning from Effurun when the incident took place. The two deceased mechan­ics were said to be fixing a broken down truck along the Expressway when they were crushed by the speeding Lex­us 350 Jeep. The two mechanics that died on the spot were dis­membered. It took the ef­forts of sympathizers who thronged the scene of the ac­cident to pick up the dismem­bered bodies of the victims. The injured victims in­cluding the suspected yahoo boy were rushed to the Sam­uel Jereton Mariere Central hospital, Ughelli for treat­ment. An eye witness told our correspondent that the driv­er of the Lexus 350 Jeep is believed to be a learner. POLL The remains of the vic­tims were deposited at a morgue in Ughelli. When contacted, the spokesman of the Delta State Police Command, DPS Bright Edafe, said he has not been briefed of the incident. In another development, a suspected Yahoo boy killed his girlfriend for money rit­ual in Sapele Local Govern­ment Area of Delta State, over the weekend. He alleged­ly slaughtered his girlfriend for a money ritual. The in­cident reportedly occurred when the suspect, after sleep­ing with his now deceased girlfriend in the night, went ahead to slaughter her while she was fast asleep. Report says the Yahoo boy had been boasting he would soon buy a Venza car, since his friend bought one, and that the urge for Venza prompted him to kill his girlfriend.